HEADWORD: Rhymer
<hw>Rhym"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who makes rhymes;
a versifier; -- generally in contempt; a poor poet; a
poetaster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This would make them soon perceive what despicaple creatures our
common <qex>rhymers</qex> and playwriters be.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhymery</ent>⟦br⟧
